    <section class="page-hero">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label"><i class="fas fa-plus-circle"></i> Host Guide</span>
            <h1>How to Add Your Charger on ChargeKr</h1>
            <p>Learn how to list your EV charger, set availability, and earn money by sharing it with nearby drivers.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
        <div class="container container--narrow">
            <div class="card reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
                <h2>Step 1: Register and verify</h2>
                <p>Create a ChargeKr account, complete the profile, and verify your identity. Verification helps build trust for drivers who want to book your charger.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
                <h2>Step 2: Add charger details</h2>
                <p>Enter your charger type, connector type, power rating, and location. Upload clear photos and share any access instructions so drivers can find and use your charger easily.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
                <h2>Step 3: Set pricing and availability</h2>
                <p>Choose a competitive per-kWh or hourly rate, and set the hours when your charger is available. You can block off times when the charger is reserved for personal use.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="card reveal" style="margin-bottom:40px;">
                <h2>Step 4: Start receiving bookings</h2>
                <p>Once your charger is live, nearby EV drivers can find it, book a slot, and pay through the app. ChargeKr handles the booking process so you can focus on hosting.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="text-center" style="margin-top:24px;">
